# Supernova Arcade — environment variables
#
# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev, or set these in the Vercel project
# (Project Settings -> Environment Variables). NEVER commit real secrets.

# --- Gasless relayer signing key (REQUIRED for onchain plays) ---
# The /api/relay route co-signs player transactions (Relayed v3) and pays the
# testnet gas. Set EXACTLY ONE of these to the relayer wallet. Without it the
# route returns 503 relayer_unavailable and games still play locally.
#
# Use the SAME relayer wallet as the bon-dashboard / supernova-sprint.xyz deploy
# (it is safe to reuse: the player's ephemeral key is the tx sender, so two
# deployments co-signing never collide; the one shared resource is the relayer
# gas balance — keep it funded).
#
# Option A — full PEM file contents (recommended):
# RELAYER_PEM="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY for erd1...-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY for erd1...-----"
#
# Option B — 64-hex secret key:
# RELAYER_SECRET_KEY=

# --- Optional public overrides (defaults are baked into src/lib/onchain/*.config.ts) ---
# The relayer route verifies the configured signing key resolves to this address.
# Only set this if you swap to a different relayer wallet (must match the key above).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_RELAYER_ADDRESS=erd1ru08dt4u5e0psfrwth38u0dfed0hw8289xqdd9yghl3ec24uppuq6hgphm

# Contract address overrides (defaults are the live testnet shard-0 deploys).
# Set only if a contract is redeployed. The public client mirror lives in
# public/arcade-core.js (static cabinets can't read NEXT_PUBLIC at runtime), so
# update both if you change an address.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_LEADERBOARD_CONTRACT=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ONCHAIN_LEADERBOARD_CONTRACT=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TAP_COUNTER_CONTRACT=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TUGOFWAR_CONTRACT=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CANVAS_CONTRACT=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BUTTON_CONTRACT=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_REACTION_CONTRACT=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLAWBACK_CONTRACT=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEGENDASH_CONTRACT=
